OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA cloudy start with a little
OL,6,Fdrizzle away from the southwest.
OL,7,FOtherwise a dry day with cloud
OL,8,Fgradually breaking to give some
OL,9,Fsunshine during the afternoon. Best of
OL,10,Fthe sunshine across Skye and Lochaber.
OL,11,FWarm in the southwest.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FThis evening will be dry with
OL,14,Fsome late sunshine. The rest of the
OL,15,Fnight will be dry with patchy low
OL,16,Fcloud and fog in the east. Cold with
OL,17,Fpatchy frost.
OL,18,
OL,19,CThursday:FOvernight mist and low cloud
OL,20,Fsoon clearing to leave a dry day with
OL,21,Fplenty of sunshine. Warm by afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
